nodes.body: @xroblot Do you see a quick way of proving that if `finrank K = 1` then  `NrRealPlaces K = 1`?

> @xroblot Do you see a quick way of proving that if `finrank K = 1` then `NrRealPlaces K = 1`?

Well, I don't see a better way than to use [NumberField.InfinitePlace.card_add_two_mul_card_eq_rank](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/Embeddings.html#NumberField.InfinitePlace.card_add_two_mul_card_eq_rank) but I am sure you know that already. 

Well, there might something possible using: [IsUnramifiedAtInfinitePlaces_of_odd_finrank](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/Embeddings.html#IsUnramifiedAtInfinitePlaces_of_odd_finrank). It could be a bit faster... I am not sure.

> > @xroblot Do you see a quick way of proving that if `finrank K = 1` then `NrRealPlaces K = 1`?
> 
> Well, I don't see a better way than to use [NumberField.InfinitePlace.card_add_two_mul_card_eq_rank](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/Embeddings.html#NumberField.InfinitePlace.card_add_two_mul_card_eq_rank) but I am sure you know that already.
> 
> Well, there might something possible using: [IsUnramifiedAtInfinitePlaces_of_odd_finrank](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/Embeddings.html#IsUnramifiedAtInfinitePlaces_of_odd_finrank). It could be a bit faster... I am not sure.

Ah, you're right! I didn't realize that [NumberField.InfinitePlace.card_add_two_mul_card_eq_rank](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/Embeddings.html#NumberField.InfinitePlace.card_add_two_mul_card_eq_rank) immediately gives a + 2*b = 1 so a = 1 and b = 0!
I've generalized the fact that `NrComplexPlaces K = Ï† n / 2` without the assumption that `2 < n` (of course it holds for stupid reasons, but still).
Besides the two golfing, LGTM.

Thanks :tada:

bors merge

I just meant you can replace line 1010 by 
```lean
rwa [Complex.norm_eq_abs, â† him, â† abs_one, abs_eq_abs] at this
``` 
and delete the following lines.
BTW, I'd be interested to know what people use to write their review since I cannot figure out how to do it properly ðŸ˜…

```suggestion
    exact hÎ¶'.ne_one (by linarith) <| Complex.ext (by simp [hone]) (by simp [him])
```
And here there is a`refine` that should be an `exact`.

```suggestion
  Â· have : Ï† n = 1 := by
      by_cases h1 : 1 < n.1
      Â· convert totient_two
        exact (eq_of_le_of_not_lt (succ_le_of_lt h1) hn).symm
      Â· convert totient_one
        rw [â† PNat.one_coe, PNat.coe_inj]
        exact eq_of_le_of_not_lt (not_lt.mp h1) (PNat.not_lt_one _)
    rw [this]
    apply nrComplexPlaces_eq_zero_of_finrank_eq_one
    rw [IsCyclotomicExtension.finrank K (cyclotomic.irreducible_rat n.pos), this]
```

```suggestion

```
Wow, `linarith` is smater than I thought!
